message.content: cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.COMM, cs.DC, cs.SY - The paper discusses the design and implementation issues for providing minimum rate guarantees to the ATM Unspecified Bit Rate (UBR) service, which is a networking protocol. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses buffer management and policing mechanisms, which are related to computer security (cs.CR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of GFR to support the Internet Controlled Load Service, which is related to communication and information theory (cs.COMM) and systems and control (cs.SY).
